<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-02-26T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-02-26T17:00:00-05:00" n="663" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d663">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">611.1731/165a: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Lane</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-02-26T17:00:00-05:00">February 26, 1936—5
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>18. Schedule I has not yet been received. Cable when you mailed and when
                            due here.</p>
                        <p>Interdepartmental committees considering Schedule II today and we hope to
                            be able to give you final answer on this late this afternoon or tomorrow
                            morning.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>